steps: Cycle on a bike

exercises.name: Running
steps: Run

steps: Row

exercises.name: Burpees
steps: Row

exercises.name: Incline Hammer Curls
steps: Seat yourself on incline bench with dumbbell in each hand. Back press firmly against seat with feet flat on the floor.
Allow the dumbbells to hang straight down by your side, holding with a neutral grip
Initiate movement by flexing the elbow, keeping the upper arm stationary and breathe out
Continue to the top of the movement, then slowly return to start position while breathing in

exercises.name: Wide-grip Barbell Curl
steps: Stand with your torso upright holding the barbell at the outer handle
Keep palm of your hands facing forward and elbows not flared
Keeping your upper arms stationary contract your biceps while breathing out
Continue movement until biceps are fully contracted and barbell is around shoulder height
Slowly lower the barbell whilst breathing in to finish exercise

exercises.name: Close-grip Barbell Curl
steps: Stand with your torso upright holding the barbell at the inner handle
Keep palm of your hands facing forward and elbows not flared
Keeping your upper arms stationary contract your biceps while breathing out
Continue movement until biceps are fully contracted and barbell is around shoulder height
Slowly lower the barbell whilst breathing in to finish exercise

exercises.name: Barbell Curl
steps: Stand with your torso upright holding the barbell at the neutral/middle handle
Keep palm of your hands facing forward and elbows not flared
Keeping your upper arms stationary contract your biceps while breathing out
Continue movement until biceps are fully contracted and barbell is around shoulder height
Slowly lower the barbell whilst breathing in to finish exercise

exercises.name: EZ-Bar Spider Curl
steps: Place bench at a secure 45 degree angle
Face towards the bench and lift EZ bar over the back of the headrest and pressing your torso and stomach against the backrest
Keeping your upper arms stationary contract your biceps while breathing out
Continue movement until biceps are fully contracted and barbell is near your chin
Slowly lower the barbell whilst breathing in to finish exercise

exercises.name: Hammer Curls
steps: Either standing or seating, keep torso upright
With dumbbells held by your side with palms facing in
Alternately or simulataneously contract your biceps whilst not rotating palms and breating out
Continue movement until biceps are fully contracted and dumbbell is around shoulder height
Slowly lower the dumbbell whilst breathing in to finish exercise

exercises.name: Zottman Curl
steps: Stand with torso upright with dumbbell in each hand held at arms length, keeping elbows in
With your upper arms stationary, contract your biceps as your breathe out
Continue until biceps are fully contracted and hold for a second
Rotate wrists so your palms are facing down, with biceps still full contracted
Slowly lower the dumbbell whilst breathing in, and turn wrists back to original position as they approach your thighs

exercises.name: Concentration Curl
steps: Sit on a bench with one dumbbell in front of you between your legs
Hold the dumbbell with your upper arm against your thigh
Contract your bicep whilst breathing out, keeping upper arm stationary and trying best not to swing
When bicep is fully contracted, slowly lower your arm whilst breating in, returning to original postion

exercises.name: Machine Bicep Curl
steps: Adjust seat and sit comfortably on the machine with your triceps flat against the padding
Grip the handles and contract biceps whilst breating out
When bicep is fully contracted, slowly lower your arm whilst breating in, returning to original postion

exercises.name: Overhead Cable Curl
steps: Stand between cable machien with cable positions just above shoulder height
Whilst keeping elbows inline with the cables, contract biceps until cable handles are next to you head
When bicep is fully contracted, slowly lower your arm whilst breating in, returning to original postion

exercises.name: Cross-body Hammer Curl
steps: Stand with torso upright with dumbbell in each hand held at arms length, keeping elbows in
Contract your biceps as your breathe out, bringing the dumbbell across your body to the opposing shoulder
Slowly lower the dumbbell whilst breathing in, and turn wrists back to original position as they approach your thighs

exercises.name: Preacher Curl
steps: Adjust seat and sit comfortably on the preacher curl seat with your triceps flat against the padding
Grip the handles and contract biceps whilst breating out, without flaring elbows
When bicep is fully contracted, slowly lower your arm whilst breating in, returning to original postion

exercises.name: Stand Biceps Cable Curl
steps: Stand between cable machien with cable positions at the bottom
Whilst keeping elbows by your side, contract biceps until cable handles are by your shoulders
When bicep is fully contracted, slowly lower your arm whilst breating in, returning to original postion

exercises.name: Tricep Dips
steps: Hold you body at arms length with your arms nearly locked above the bars
Inhale as you lower yourself down, keeping your torso upright and elbows close to your body
When your arms reach a 90 degree angle, exhale as your push your body back up to the start position

exercises.name: EZ-bar Skullcrusher
steps: Laying on a bench using a close grip, hold the bar above your head.
As you breathe in, and keeping your arms stationary, bring the bar down moving your forearms in a semicircular motion until the bar reaches your forehead.
Breathe out, while returning the bar to the previous position reversing the action

exercises.name: Decline EZ-bar Skullcrusher
steps: Laying on a bench using a close grip, hold the bar above your head.
As you breathe in, and keeping your arms stationary, bring the bar down moving your forearms in a semicircular motion until the bar reaches your forehead
Breathe out, while returning the bar to the previous position reversing the action

exercises.name: Cable V-bar Push-down
steps: Postion yourself leaning slightly foreward using an overhand grip on the v-bar.
Using your triceps while breathing out, bring the bar down until it reaches your thighs and arms are perpendicular to the floor, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Hold at the contracted position for a moment and slowly move the v-bar back to the starting position while breathing in

exercises.name: Single-arm Cable Triceps Extension
steps: Placing the cable in a high position, grip the handle using a supinated grip
Pull the handle down so that your upper arm and elbow are locked to the side of your body
While breating out and contracting the tricep, move the single handle attachment down to your side until your arm is fully extended, your upper arms should remain stationary
Slowly return handle to the startig positon as your breathe in

exercises.name: Triceps Dumbbell Kickback
steps: Whilst holding a dumbbell by your side with your arm at an acute angle with your upper arm parallel to your side
Breathe out while you contract your arm pushing the tricep back, your arm should now be straight and parallel to your side
Breathe in as your return to your starting position

exercises.name: Palm-down Wrist Curl
steps: With you forearms resting perpendicular to a seat of a bench, hold the dumbbell with a pronated grip, your wrists should hang over the edge
Curl your wrist upwards while breathing out
Hold for a moment and breathe in as your return to the starting position

exercises.name: Straight-bar Wrist Roll-up
steps: Holding the barbell directly infront of you, alternate turning your wrists, twisting the bar forewards or backwards

exercises.name: Dumbbell Farmer's Walk
steps: Lift the dumbbells to your side
Walk forewards, keeping a strong grip of the dumbbells

exercises.name: Muscle Up
steps: Initiate a pull up whilst breating out, pulling your elbows down to your side
When you've reached the top position of the pull up, roll your shoulders foreward and push yourself up with a dip like action

exercises.name: Pullups
steps: Hang freely from a pull up bar with arms fully extended.
Whilst breathing out, flex your elbows and pull yourself up. Try not to swing or use momentum to complete the movement
Attempt to get your chin above your hands
Lower yourself to the starting position whilst breathing out.

exercises.name: Weighted Pullups
steps: Hang freely from a pull up bar with arms fully extended.
Whilst breathing out, flex your elbows and pull yourself up. Try not to swing or use momentum to complete the movement
Attempt to get your chin above your hands
Lower yourself to the starting position whilst breathing out.
